The paper deals with the problem of detecting symmetries in 3D shapes, which is a common topic in computer graphics and computer vision. The use of volumetric shape representations and the evaluation on the COSEG data-set suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The algorithmic and computational aspects of the paper, as well as the use of sampling and approximation techniques, suggest that it could also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
